    <name>
				<text>1.4.3.2 Add fractions 1</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>

<p>Simplify</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>\(\displaystyle {@exp1@} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</li>
    <li>\(\displaystyle {@exp2@} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</li>
    <li>\(\displaystyle {@exp3@} = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</li>
    <li>\(\displaystyle {@exp4@} = \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <p>Both denominators are simply numbers. The lowest common denominator is {@ev(a1*a2,simp)@}, and both fractions are re-written with this denominator:</p>
        <p>\(\displaystyle {@exp1@} = \dfrac{@a2*v@}{@ev(a1*a2,simp)@} + \dfrac{@a1*v@}{@ev(a1*a2, simp)@} = {@ta1@}\)</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>Both denominators are simply numbers. The lowest common denominator is {@ev(b1*b2, simp)@}, and both fractions are re-written with this denominator:</p>
        <p>\(\displaystyle {@exp2@} = \dfrac{@ev(2*v*b2, simp)@}{@ev(b1*b2, simp)@} - \dfrac{@ev(b1*b1*v,simp)@}{@ev(b1*b2, simp)@} = {@ta2@}\)</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>The lowest common denominator is the product of the denominators, {@ev(v*(v+2),simp)@}. Thus writing both fractions with the same denominator we have:</p>
        <p>\(\displaystyle {@exp3@} = \dfrac{@ev((v+1)*(v+2), simp)@}{@ev(v*(v+2),simp)@} + \dfrac{@ev(c1*v,simp)@}{@ev(v*(v+2),simp)@} = {@ta3@}\)</p>
    </li>

    <li>
        <p>The lowest common denominator is the product of the denominators, {@ev((v+1)*(v+d2),simp)@}. Thus writing both fractions with the same denominator we have:</p>
        <p>\(\displaystyle {@exp4@} = \dfrac{@ev(v*(v+d2), simp)@}{@ev((v+1)*(v+d2),simp)@} - \dfrac{@ev(d1*(v+1),simp)@}{@ev((v+1)*(v+d2),simp)@} = {@ta4@}\)</p>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
